    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making this weird humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. what's probably wrong with it and is it safe to poke around in there?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A weird humming noise with a fan that won't spin is a classic sign of a **capacitor failure** or a **motor bearing issue**, which is essentially the AC unit's heart stopping while its lungs (the compressor) are still trying to breathe. It's definitely not safe to poke around inside the unit without proper tools and training, as the capacitors can still hold a lethal charge even when the power is off, and the fan blades can spin unexpectedly if you touch them while the unit is on.\n\nYou should turn off the power at the breaker immediately and call a professional HVAC technician to diagnose the problem, as they have the specific tools to safely replace the faulty capacitor or repair the motor. Trying to fix this yourself is like trying to catch a runaway train with your bare hands; it's too dangerous and likely to result in more expensive repairs later.\n\nIn the meantime, keep the area clear of debris and avoid touching any wires or components inside the cabinet. If you see any signs of burning or smoke, evacuate the area and call emergency services right away. It's always better to let the experts handle the job, just like a good team of goblins would handle a dangerous situation.\n\n**Safety First:**\n*",
